Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Individual Empowerment Organization

feedback.survey: This was a great survey, I like when they make me think of others and things not normally asked about. It was easy to follow and understand.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: They will spend the money on daily requirements for life--food, clothing, perhaps health care, etc.  A few may be able to spend the money on items which would have long term benefits, but with such low incomes it's unlikely that they can afford NOT to spend it on daily necessities.
feedback.survey: Not confusing or no comments on the survey (except that it makes me sad and guilty when I think of my relative comfort).  I make less than $15K annually, but that's relatively rich when compared to others who lack any real resources.

This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization
feedback.survey: was interesting, thank you for the opportunity!

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: Hopefully food, shelter, clothing and other necessities
feedback.survey: Thank you for allowing my participation in your survey

usemoney: Food, shelter, and the smartest of the groups will continue their life and save a buck or two down the line.
feedback.survey: I'm not sure if this is aid will be of a significant use other than short term changes in local economy. Is the money spent on this, just handed out? Or are the recipients learning something to be used after the aid has run dry? I'm all for giving people money to attain a better life, but I'm more worried about what happens to that local economy if the organisation just suddenly stops.

This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization
usemoney: Food, shalter and other basic needs.

The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

usemoney: I have no idea... food, perhaps a small improvement at home, or may well be luxury items?  Not that's particularly a bad thing.  But I don't imagine many will have something specific that $2 will buy in their country that's going to revolutionize their lives, though I don't know.  Perhaps healthcare needs if they have any which could be important/helpful.
feedback.survey: The options of either "They are poor because of laziness and lack of willpower or They are poor because society treats them unfairly. was harsh.  I don't come close to thinking either.  They were born into tougher circumstances, and haven't managed to get the innovation/bump in life that unlocks that situation.  All struggled at lower levels once (well, the majority, certainly not the monarchs and such, but pre-Industrial Revolution, most were in the same circumstances that folks living in poorer slums still are)... technology and innovation (partially luck, partially effort) unlocked life more for some, which has gradually expanded to benefit many... but it has not reached those born into and struggling in slums.  In places like America and Europe people born in poorer areas do have some opportunity to improve their lives.  But a person in a slum in Nairobi indeed doesn't have much opportunity to better their lives.  They might be able to work up to escape the slums to a better situation in Kenya or Africa.  But it's not like they'll be getting the bright situations even the poorest see in America/Europe (and parts of northern/eastern Asia, Australia, parts of South America, South Africa, etc).  So for these struggling in Kenya, I don't see either answer as representing my opinion whatsoever.  There are people who try to help those in the rougher situations.  Gradually a lot of the world has found things improving as a collective.  But I don't see it PRIMARILY being society taking advantage/mistreating the poor of the world (because the majority of the poor in the world are in such slums... such that even though I barely scrape life together in the US, I know I'm still in the top few percentage of the world).  There are those who make money off the backs of others, and they're relatively detestable in general... but they're not the cause of the poor's situation in general (as indeed, the poorness state was the default, and is slowly eroding), but just could be a bit better help to some... but I'm not sure if all the greed in the world were turned to lifting the poor around the world, people like the ones mentioned in African slums and rural poor areas would be suddenly in truly great lives.  So there's not a ton most poor (in most parts of the world) can do to turn things around, because numerically there will be poor with the current value of the world, apart from something more socialist (which may well not work to benefit well anyways)... but it's also not a large part because of people taking advantage of them/treating them unfairly.  It's the way it is mathematically, and things are gradually improving as more innovation happens... we do need to make sure benefits of new advances can spread to lift the many too and not just create opulence for few in coming centuries, as there will be a desire for the elite to yet further grow their "kingdoms"... but as it is now I don't see things being horribly done.  And so neither option represents my thinking much at all.

The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Individual Empowerment Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization
usemoney: I would hope on necessities like food and clothes.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Individual Empowerment Organization
usemoney: Thats where I disagree with this organization and why I am not willing to donate more money...I do not agree that just giving them money to Perdue their goals is a good idea.  People need guidance as to how to spend it. With little education the odds of using it wisely are slim. Some may buy food, alcohol, spend it on frivolous things. What should be done with it is open a trade school to educate people ways they can improve their lives and how to do it.  Just giving money is not the answer. I feel they will waste it on foolish things as stated earlier.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization
feedback.survey: I found the first comprehension check confusing. I wasn't entirely sure if it was asking how much the people earn on their own or how much they'd be getting from the organization. In the article, it said they live on less than $2 a day, so I chose "less than $2" for the question.

The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:

They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: I would hope they would use it for food, dressing and sending their children to school, starting a small business, of natural home crafts indigenous to East Africa, or clean water efforts.  The Organization needs to have locals in the villages to suggest who to give the money to, or it could be used for drugs, alcohol, oppressing women and girls, or human trafficking.  Thank you.
feedback.survey: It is always risky to just give cash to individuals. In an ideal world we would want people in need to use the money to help themselves their family and community. / There will be some who misuse the money, that is why there needs to be oversight on who gets the money.  / It might be better to set up schools, drug programs, programs to educate about treatment of women, rape, how to own your own business in the community, then give the cash through those organizations, and then you would be able to target the individuals or families that are motivated to really get out of the slums, or who need the help to find their way out.  Thank you.

text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. feedback.survey: I was very tempted to say that I would donate the money but the truth is that this doesn't sound like a good organization. Giving someone two days pay is nice, but it isn't quite enough to make any lasting change. If they were given $40, I would have been more likely to give something because it would may actually help. As for now, I will stick with places where my money can do the most good.

The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: They will spend the money on helping their community and their families.
feedback.survey: I appreciated the opportunity to participate on your very touching and relevant survey!

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Individual Empowerment Organization
usemoney: Something that they believe will make their life better in some way.
feedback.survey: I do not have any feedback.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: Nothing that will "improve" their lives in any longterm signifigant way. perhaps more food for the day or some basic household nessecities or medicine. What good does it for people from half way around the world to pour money on these people when they cant get value out of their closest neighbors. There's something clearly wrong with the free market when these seemingly ablebodied people somehow cant exchange their labour for money in someway.
feedback.survey: We should work on not needing "charities" at all instead of constantly trying to figure out why someone would be against giving them money.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization
feedback.survey: No; all was clear.  Thank you for your research and for caring and sharing!

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: They will spend the money on things necessary for them to live on, things like foods, water, and/or items for their homes.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

feedback.survey: The answers offered for the question about the amount a person earns per day were ambiguous. The wage was reported as $2 per day; but the people often live on less than $2 per day. I marked the answer "Less than $2 Per day" as the daily wage, because the next option was "$2 to $4 per day" which, to my mind, would have been incorrect. Perhaps I misunderstood.  Thanks for the chance to participate.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Individual Empowerment Organization

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

Some people are born in poverty and it is very hard to overcome that.  Others are too lazy to work because they know they can live off welfare in the United States.  If people have the health and opportunity to work, then I firmly believe in "no work, no eat".

The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Individual Empowerment Organization
usemoney: To help those in need in the slums of Kenya.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization

text:

The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

text:
The goal of the Poverty Alleviation Organization is to alleviate poverty and reduce financial hardship among the poor. This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization

feedback.survey: People who give to international organizations on a regular basis likely are going to compare the mission statement and strategy of the (hypothetical?) organization you describe in the study with the organizations they already support. Will what you are trying to measure be skewed by a person stating they will not donate any money to the organization named specifically because they believe the $100 (or whatever potion they'd choose to donate) will be better spent/invested by a different organization? If so, you need to add a third option (I will donate to x dollars to another organization).

This organization believes that people living in poverty should be given income support to help them meet their basic needs. This organization aims to help promote a decent standard of living among the poor and help them deal with emergencies.

Thus, the Poverty Alleviation Organization gives financial assistance to people to help them make ends meet. For example, with the financial assistance, people might be able to struggle less to afford basic needs, like paying off debts, paying rent, and buying clothes and food.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial assistance to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Poverty Alleviation Organization
usemoney: basic needs and a little extra

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Community Empowerment Organization is to enable people to help promote better futures for those they care about and want to support most. The organization believes that people know best how to support each other and grow together if they have financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower people to improve their own lives and those of the people and communities they care about most.

Thus, the Community Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to community members to enable them to contribute positively to the lives of people important to them. For example, when people can invest in themselves, they are better able to expand employment opportunities for others, provide valuable services to their community, or teach others, including children, useful skills and knowledge.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.
name: Community Empowerment Organization
usemoney: I think they will spend the money on improving lives for people.

Name: Anonymous
text:
The goal of the Individual Empowerment Organization is to promote individuals' potential to create a better future for themselves. The organization believes that individuals are wise and know best how to help themselves become self-reliant if they have the financial resources to do so. This organization aims to empower individuals to pursue their personal interests and create their own path to independence.

Thus, the Individual Empowerment Organization gives financial resources to individuals to enable them to invest in their personal goals. For example, people might use their unique talents to start a self-run business, invest in job training courses, or create art.

Towards that mission, this nonprofit gives one-time transfers of financial resources to people in urban slums in Nairobi, Kenya, East Africa. They give each recipient $4 USD (about two days wages) in cash. These program recipients are people who live on less than $2 per day, and half of recipients have no savings.

feedback.survey: The survey was very clear. I generally do not believe in giving individuals small influxes of cash. The system/government itself is usually to blame for poverty. I would rather the non-profit acted on behalf of the public be it a clinic, vocational training,  heath center, or food bank. Giving to an individual doesn't seem all that helpful to a community as a whole.
